3.10	Hysteria_(Def_Leppard_song)	Hysteria (Def Leppard song)	"Hysteria" is a song by British hard rock band Def Leppard. It served as the titular third single from their 1987 multi-platinum album of the same name. "Hysteria" peaked at #10 on the Billboard Hot 100. On VH1 Storytellers: Def Leppard, frontman Joe Elliott revealed that the song title came from drummer Rick Allen.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b6/Def_Leppard_hysteria_single_2.jpg/220px-Def_Leppard_hysteria_single_2.jpg
